"title": "5542: society, positive aspects of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5542: society, positive aspects of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The object of God's love and the sphere of God's blessing. God's people should adopt a positive but critical attitude to, and involvement in society, and should seek to influence it for good, while guarding against its corrupting influence.</p>\n<h2>Society is the object of God's redeeming love and the sphere of his blessing</h2>\n<h3>The city as a positive image of society</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:26-Isa1:27\">ISA 1:26–1:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps122:6-Ps122:9\">PSA 122:6–122:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:11-Isa54:14\">ISA 54:11–54:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:10\">HEB 11:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:15-Heb11:16\">HEB 11:15–11:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:1-Rev21:4\">REV 21:1–21:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:22-Rev22:5\">REV 21:22–22:5</a></p>\n<h3>The world as the object of God's love</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:16-John3:17\">JHN 3:16–3:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:33\">JHN 6:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:19\">2CO 5:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:14\">1JN 4:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev11:15\">REV 11:15</a></p>\n<h2>God's people are to be positively involved in society</h2>\n<h3>They are to seek to be a positive influence</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:15-John17:18\">JHN 17:15–17:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer29:7\">JER 29:7</a> <em>God's people, in exile in Babylon, are to seek the welfare of that society, rather than simply long to return home</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:13-Matt5:16\">MAT 5:13–5:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:9-1Cor5:10\">1CO 5:9–5:10</a></p>\n<h3>They are to avoid being corrupted by society's worldliness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:27\">JAS 1:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:2\">ROM 12:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:4\">JAS 4:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:15-1John2:17\">1JN 2:15–2:17</a></p>\n<h3>They do not owe society their ultimate loyalty</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:16\">JHN 17:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:19\">JHN 15:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:14\">HEB 13:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:11\">1PE 2:11</a></p>\n<h3>They are to adopt a positive attitude to society's properly instituted authorities</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:1-Rom13:7\">ROM 13:1–13:7</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:1\">TIT 3:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:17-Matt22:21\">MAT 22:17–22:21</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:14-Mark12:17\">MRK 12:14–12:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:22-Luke20:25\">LUK 20:22–20:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:13-1Pet2:17\">1PE 2:13–2:17</a></p>\n<h3>While being submissive, they are not to give absolute obedience to any merely human authority in society</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:18-Acts4:20\">ACT 4:18–4:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:27-Acts5:29\">ACT 5:27–5:29</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of those positively involved in society</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:48-Dan2:49\">DAN 2:48–2:49</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:41-Gen41:49\">GEN 41:41–41:49</a> <em>Joseph</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth10:1-Esth10:3\">EST 10:1–10:3</a> <em>Mordecai</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan1:1-Dan1:21\">DAN 1:1–1:21</a> <em>Daniel and his friends</em></p>",
